{
  "texts": [
    "In the realm of university-level science and engineering, SCIBENCH (Wang et al, 2023d) is tailor-made to evaluate LLMs' capabilities, demanding the resolution of challenging subjective questions related to mathematics, physics, and chemistry.",
    "TheoremQA (Chen et al, 2023b) narrows its focus to 350 theorems from mathematics, physics, finance, and CS & EE (Computer Science & Electrical Engineering).",
    "Lastly, ARB (Sawada et al, 2023) introduces a more demanding examination, appraising LLMs' prowess in text comprehension and domain-specific reasoning.",
    "The questions delve into profound knowledge across disciplines such as mathematics, physics, biology, chemistry, and law.",
    "The aforementioned datasets focus on evaluating specific disciplines on a smaller scale."
  ]
}